AB  - A simple compact but general revealed-preference type of argument is used to derive results on the gains from trade, from terms of trade changes, and from exogenous resource growth. The approach extends to the welfare evaluation of public sector production. The relation between the sufficiency conditions for welfare improvement derived from this approach and the necessary and sufficient conditions derived in an alternative approach are briefly discussed. Most of the argument is conducted in the context of a representative-individual economy, though it is shown to extend in an essentially unchanged way to cases where redistribution is an issue.
